article.headline: Holy Cross 68, Iona 55
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- John Hurley had 15 points and 11 rebounds, and Keith Simmons added 11 points to lead Holy Cross past Iona 68-55 on Wednesday. The Crusaders (5-6) shot just 37.9 percent (22-for-58) from the field, but were able to limit the Gaels to 31.4 percent shooting (16-for-51). DeShaun Williams had 14 points and nine rebounds for Iona (3-7), which also got 14 points from Steve Smith. Nate Lufkin added 10 points for Holy Cross.
